Nova Measuring Advances Most in Two Weeks on $12 Million Orders

-- B y   D a v i d   W a i n e r
-- 
2011-03-03T09:39:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-03/nova-measuring-advances-most-in-two-weeks-on-12-million-orders.html
  Nova Measuring Instruments Ltd. (NVMI)  rose
the most in more than two weeks after the maker of measuring
instruments for the semiconductor industry received $12 million
of orders from three foundries.  The shares increased 6.4 percent, the most since Feb. 15,
to 34.85 shekels as of 11:26 a.m. in  Tel Aviv .  Nova said the tools are expected to be delivered within the
first half of this year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
David Wainer in Tel Aviv at 
 dwainer1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler in Dubai at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net . 